jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 480w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-greens-pasta-pcbm/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-greens-pasta-pcbm-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 768w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-greens-pasta-pcbm/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-greens-pasta-pcbm-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1024w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-greens-pasta-pcbm/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-greens-pasta-pcbm-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1280w\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-greens-pasta-pcbm/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-greens-pasta-pcbm-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eArmando Rafael for The New York Times. Food Stylist: Cyd Raftus McDowell.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eThis elemental pasta brings together rotisserie chicken, chopped greens and pasta (make it whole-grain if you like) with a silky sauce that invites tailoring: The cream is optional, and you can use olive oil in place of butter. Christian Reynoso reminds us of one cardinal rotisserie rule: Season the meat as you would anything else (here, with salt and pepper).\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eRecipe: \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1023870-rotisserie-chicken-and-greens-pasta\" title=\"\"\u003eRotisserie Chicken and Greens Pasta\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"link-54fac68b\"\u003e4. \u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1023286-crispy-wonton-chicken-salad\" title=\"\"\u003eCrispy Wonton Chicken Salad\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"An overhead image of a blue bowl filled with greens, wonton strips and chicken.\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-WONTON-SALAD-mqjh/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-WONTON-SALAD-mqjh-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 320w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-WONTON-SALAD-mqjh/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-WONTON-SALAD-mqjh-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 480w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-WONTON-SALAD-mqjh/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-WONTON-SALAD-mqjh-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 768w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-WONTON-SALAD-mqjh/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-WONTON-SALAD-mqjh-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1024w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-WONTON-SALAD-mqjh/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-WONTON-SALAD-mqjh-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1280w\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-WONTON-SALAD-mqjh/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-WONTON-SALAD-mqjh-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eChris Simpson for The New York Times. Food stylist: Maggie Ruggiero. Prop stylist: Sophia Pappas.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eEric Kim’s paean to the very ’90s Chinese chicken salad is tangier, crunchier and more adaptable than you remember. Dial up different flavors by adding extra herbs, sliced almonds, julienned carrots or mandarin slices.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eRecipe: \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1023286-crispy-wonton-chicken-salad\" title=\"\"\u003eCrispy Wonton Chicken Salad\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"link-79e5e735\"\u003e5. \u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1024345-white-chicken-chili\" title=\"\"\u003eWhite Chicken Chili\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Two bowls of white chicken chili with sliced avocado, corn, red onions, jalapeños and lime slices.\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Chili-vjgq/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Chili-vjgq-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 320w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Chili-vjgq/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Chili-vjgq-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 480w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Chili-vjgq/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Chili-vjgq-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 768w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Chili-vjgq/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Chili-vjgq-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1024w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Chili-vjgq/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Chili-vjgq-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1280w\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Chili-vjgq/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Chili-vjgq-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eChristopher Testani for The New York Times. Food Stylist: Simon Andrews.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eYes, chili can be light and healthy — and quick, when aided by a handy rotisserie chicken. Lidey Heuck’s recipe unites a creamy white bean base with canned green chiles, pops of corn and morsels of chicken for an everyday, easy-listening kind of chili. Make a moment of it with a toppings bar of cilantro, tortilla chips and fresh chiles.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eRecipe: \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1024345-white-chicken-chili\" title=\"\"\u003eWhite Chicken Chili\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"link-23fc54f\"\u003e6. \u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1024528-green-goddess-chicken-salad-sandwiches\" title=\"\"\u003eGreen Goddess Chicken Salad Sandwiches\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A green goddess chicken salad cut in half sits on a wooden cutting board.\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-green-goddess-qtjg/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-green-goddess-qtjg-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 320w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-green-goddess-qtjg/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-green-goddess-qtjg-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 480w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-green-goddess-qtjg/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-green-goddess-qtjg-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 768w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-green-goddess-qtjg/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-green-goddess-qtjg-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1024w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-green-goddess-qtjg/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-green-goddess-qtjg-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1280w\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-green-goddess-qtjg/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-green-goddess-qtjg-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eJulia Gartland for The New York Times. Food Stylist: Samantha Seneviratne.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eCan a sandwich dare to be dinner? It can if it’s Lidey Heuck’s chicken salad sandwich, glammed up with avocado and green goddess dressing. Spike it with \u003ca href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/25/dining/tuna-salad-sandwich-chips.html\" title=\"\"\u003ecrushed chips\u003c/a\u003e and serve with a \u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/68861692-nyt-cooking/17098-easy-salad-recipes\" title=\"\"\u003esimple salad\u003c/a\u003e for a springtime vibe.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eRecipe: \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1024528-green-goddess-chicken-salad-sandwiches\" title=\"\"\u003eGreen Goddess Chicken Salad Sandwiches\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"link-7faa1726\"\u003e7. \u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1026473-chicken-and-red-lentil-soup-with-lemony-yogurt\" title=\"\"\u003eChicken and Red Lentil Soup With Lemony Yogurt\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Two bowls of chicken and red lentil soup with dribbles of yogurt.\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-red-lentil-soup-lfkq/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-red-lentil-soup-lfkq-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 320w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-red-lentil-soup-lfkq/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-red-lentil-soup-lfkq-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 480w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-red-lentil-soup-lfkq/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-red-lentil-soup-lfkq-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 768w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-red-lentil-soup-lfkq/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-red-lentil-soup-lfkq-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1024w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-red-lentil-soup-lfkq/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-red-lentil-soup-lfkq-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1280w\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-red-lentil-soup-lfkq/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-red-lentil-soup-lfkq-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eArmando Rafael for The New York Times. Food Stylist: Hadas Smirnoff.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eRotisserie chicken effectively halves the cooking time for this soothing lentil soup from Andy Baraghani — but you’ll want to add a rich chicken broth to compensate. Don’t skip the lemony yogurt, and do pile on chopped herbs sky-high.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eRecipe: \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1026473-chicken-and-red-lentil-soup-with-lemony-yogurt\" title=\"\"\u003eChicken and Red Lentil Soup With Lemony Yogurt\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"link-32da3aca\"\u003e8. \u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1022301-sesame-snap-pea-chicken-salad\" title=\"\"\u003eSesame Snap Pea-Chicken Salad\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A sesame snap pea chicken salad sits on a plate with two spoons.\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Sesame-Snap-Pea-hbcj/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Sesame-Snap-Pea-hbcj-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 320w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Sesame-Snap-Pea-hbcj/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Sesame-Snap-Pea-hbcj-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 480w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Sesame-Snap-Pea-hbcj/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Sesame-Snap-Pea-hbcj-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 768w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Sesame-Snap-Pea-hbcj/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Sesame-Snap-Pea-hbcj-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1024w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Sesame-Snap-Pea-hbcj/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Sesame-Snap-Pea-hbcj-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1280w\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Sesame-Snap-Pea-hbcj/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Sesame-Snap-Pea-hbcj-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eDavid Malosh for The New York Times. Food Stylist: Simon Andrews.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eBlanched snap peas, shredded chicken and one addictive sesame dressing come together in this light salad by Hana Asbrink. Commit to using Kewpie for the dressing, then commit the dressing to memory.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eRecipe: \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1022301-sesame-snap-pea-chicken-salad\" title=\"\"\u003eSesame Snap Pea Chicken Salad\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"link-4e9cdb95\"\u003e9. \u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1020217-cucumber-salad-with-roasted-peanuts-and-chile\" title=\"\"\u003eCucumber Salad With Roasted Peanuts and Chile\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A cucumber salad with peanuts and chile oil sits on a white oval platter.\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/dining/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Cucumber-Salad/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Cucumber-Salad-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 320w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/dining/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Cucumber-Salad/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Cucumber-Salad-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 480w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/dining/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Cucumber-Salad/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Cucumber-Salad-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 768w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/dining/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Cucumber-Salad/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Cucumber-Salad-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1024w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/dining/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Cucumber-Salad/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Cucumber-Salad-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1280w\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/dining/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Cucumber-Salad/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-Cucumber-Salad-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eRomulo Yanes for The New York Times. Food Stylist: Vivian Lui\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eCrisp cucumbers meet crunchy peanuts, and nutty sweetness meets numbing spice in Sue Li’s irresistible salad. It’s wonderful as is, but it’s also a welcome home for that tender rotisserie chicken. (Don’t fret about the sauce — there’s plenty.) This salad tastes great with age, though, on Day 2 or 3, it never hurts to add a fresh cuke to liven things up.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eRecipe: \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1020217-cucumber-salad-with-roasted-peanuts-and-chile\" title=\"\"\u003eCucumber Salad With Roasted Peanuts and Chile\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"link-4c0cab0b\"\u003e10. \u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1024338-chicken-noodle-soup\" title=\"\"\u003eChicken Noodle Soup\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A heavy pot filled with chicken noodle soup.\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-noodle-soup-tcgp/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-noodle-soup-tcgp-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 320w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-noodle-soup-tcgp/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-noodle-soup-tcgp-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 480w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-noodle-soup-tcgp/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-noodle-soup-tcgp-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 768w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-noodle-soup-tcgp/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-noodle-soup-tcgp-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1024w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-noodle-soup-tcgp/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-noodle-soup-tcgp-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1280w\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/02/18/multimedia/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-noodle-soup-tcgp/18ROTISSERIE-CHICKEN-noodle-soup-tcgp-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eChristopher Testani for The New York Times. Food Stylist: Simon Andrews.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe soul wants what it wants, and when it wants chicken noodle soup, it can have it any night of the week. Such is the promise of Ali Slagle’s comforting classic, all egg noodles, carrots and herbs. Use the \u003ca href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/reviews/best-boxed-chicken-broth-stock/\" title=\"\"\u003ebest stock\u003c/a\u003e you can find. And the day after, turn your fallen bird into \u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/11566-basic-chicken-stock\" title=\"\"\u003eJacques Pépin’s chicken stock\u003c/a\u003e, completing the circle.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eRecipe: \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1024338-chicken-noodle-soup\" title=\"\"\u003eChicken Noodle Soup\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eFollow \u003c/em\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.instagram.com/nytcooking/\" title=\"\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eNew York Times Cooking on Instagram\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cem\u003e, \u003c/em\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/nytcooking/\" title=\"\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eFacebook\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cem\u003e, \u003c/em\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.youtube.com/nytcooking\" title=\"\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eYouTube\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cem\u003e, \u003c/em\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.tiktok.com/@nytcooking?lang=en\" title=\"\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eTikTok\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cem\u003e and \u003c/em\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.pinterest.com/nytcooking/\" title=\"\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ePinterest\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cem\u003e. \u003c/em\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/newsletters/cooking\" title=\"\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eGet regular updates from New York Times Cooking, with recipe suggestions, cooking tips and shopping advice\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cem\u003e.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/article\u003e\u003c/main\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
